      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for explaining. i noticed you called the support side \"social progress\" and the other side \"entrenched conservative viewpoints.\" it almost sounds like you're saying one is forward-thinking and the other is just stuck in the past. do you think the concerns some parents have—like they want to be the ones to teach these values to their kids—are actually valid, or are they just being resistant to change?",
